<span id="freeTextContainer5875899640139079258"><br/>Damn good book in a damn good series.<br/><br/>This one is pretty twisty. Kenzie and Ange are still recovering from the events of the last book (<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/21681.Darkness__Take_My_Hand__Kenzie___Gennaro___2_' title='Darkness, Take My Hand (Kenzie &amp; Gennaro, #2) by Dennis Lehane' rel='nofollow noopener'>Darkness, Take My Hand</a>), when a wealthy man hires them to find his daughter.<br/><br/><i>Sacred</i> started by going off in one direction, took a brief turn toward Carl Hiassen and then settled into the feeling that our heroes had wandered into the middle of Chandler&apos;s <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2052.The_Big_Sleep' title='The Big Sleep by Raymond Chandler' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Big Sleep</a>.<br/><br/> <img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1439697775ra/15873622.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I&apos;m just sorry I finished it so quickly. </span>
