<div id="review_3075272846" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3075272846" />
    <a title="Keith Dooley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66166219-keith-dooley"><img alt="Keith Dooley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1614815918p2/66166219.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3075272846?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Keith Dooley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Keith Dooley" href="/user/show/66166219-keith-dooley">Keith Dooley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780061998867" href="/book/show/8262409-sacred">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3075272846" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4618223915852576422">3.5*<br/><br/><i>Sacred</i>, book three in the Kenzie and Gennaro series, features our protagonists searching for a billionaire&apos;s lost daughter. But since this is Lehane, nothing is as it seems and twists and turns are prevalent throughout. While I enjoy this series and look forward to the next three, I feel they do not quite reach the level of his standalone novels <i>Shutter Island</i> and <i>Mystic River</i>. </span>
  <span id="freeText4618223915852576422" style="display:none">3.5*<br /><br /><i>Sacred</i>, book three in the Kenzie and Gennaro series, features our protagonists searching for a billionaire's lost daughter. But since this is Lehane, nothing is as it seems and twists and turns are prevalent throughout. While I enjoy this series and look forward to the next three, I feel they do not quite reach the level of his standalone novels <i>Shutter Island</i> and <i>Mystic River</i>. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4618223915852576422" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


